# Real-Time Chat Backend

A scalable real-time chat backend built using Django, Django REST Framework, WebSockets (Django Channels), Redis, JWT Authentication, and Docker.

This project demonstrates how to design a real-time communication system with secure APIs and asynchronous message handling.

---

## Live Deployment

Base URL:
https://realtime-chat-backend-production-0616.up.railway.app/

WebSocket Endpoint:
wss://realtime-chat-backend-production-0616.up.railway.app/ws/chat/

---

## Overview

This backend enables real-time messaging using WebSockets while providing REST APIs for authentication and chat management.

It is designed with scalability and modularity in mind and can be extended for production-grade messaging systems.

---

## Features

### Authentication

* JWT-based authentication
* User registration and login
* Secure API access

### Real-Time Messaging

* WebSocket-based communication using Django Channels
* Instant message delivery
* Room-based chat system

### Chat Management

* One-to-one chat support
* Message persistence in database
* Easily extendable to group chats

### Performance

* Redis as channel layer
* Asynchronous handling using ASGI

### DevOps

* Dockerized setup
* Docker Compose support
* Deployment-ready configuration

---

## Architecture

```
Client
  ├── REST API → Django + DRF
  └── WebSocket → Django Channels → Redis → Database
```

---

## Tech Stack

* Python
* Django
* Django REST Framework
* Django Channels
* Redis
* JWT Authentication
* Docker & Docker Compose
* PostgreSQL / MySQL

---

## Project Structure

```
realtime-chat-backend/
│
├── chat/              # Chat logic (models, consumers, routing)
├── users/             # Authentication & user management
├── core/              # Settings and ASGI configuration
│
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── requirements.txt
└── manage.py
```

---

## Installation & Setup

### Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/MahenderJakhar27/realtime-chat-backend.git
cd realtime-chat-backend
```

---

### Environment variables

Create a `.env` file:

```env
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
DEBUG=True

DB_NAME=chat_db
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=postgres
DB_HOST=db
DB_PORT=5432

REDIS_HOST=redis
REDIS_PORT=6379

JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
```

---

### Run with Docker

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

---

### Apply migrations

```bash
docker-compose exec web python manage.py migrate
```

---

### Create superuser

```bash
docker-compose exec web python manage.py createsuperuser
```

---

## Running Locally (Without Docker)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver
```

Make sure Redis is running locally.

---

## API Usage (cURL Examples)

### Register User

```bash
curl --location 'https://realtime-chat-backend-production-0616.up.railway.app/api/register/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
    "username": "mahender",
    "email": "test@gmail.com",
    "password": "12345678"
}'
```

---

### Login User

```bash
curl --location 'https://realtime-chat-backend-production-0616.up.railway.app/api/login/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
    "username": "mahender",
    "password": "12345678"
}'
```

---

### Authenticated Request Example

```bash
curl --location 'https://realtime-chat-backend-production-0616.up.railway.app/api/chats/' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'
```

---

## API Endpoints

### Authentication

| Method | Endpoint       | Description       |
| ------ | -------------- | ----------------- |
| POST   | /api/register/ | Register user     |
| POST   | /api/login/    | Login and get JWT |

---

### Chat

| Method | Endpoint       | Description    |
| ------ | -------------- | -------------- |
| GET    | /api/chats/    | Get user chats |
| POST   | /api/messages/ | Send message   |

---

## WebSocket Workflow

1. Client connects to WebSocket endpoint
2. User joins a chat room
3. Messages are sent in real-time
4. Redis distributes messages across consumers

---

## Sample WebSocket Payload

```json
{
  "message": "Hello",
  "sender": "user1",
  "room": "room_1"
}
```

